No fewer than 30 people have been reportedly killed by armed Fulani Militia in an attack on Chibuak and Kigudu 11 Communities in Kauru Local Government area of Kaduna State. The armed Fulani Militia were said to have attacked the Communities consecutively on Thursday and Friday midnight while some of the locals got missing during the invasion. A security operative who pleaded anonymity disclosed to LEADERSHIP that as of Saturday evening not fewer than 30 people are confirmed killed. In another development, a statement signed by the Chatholic Priest of Damakasuwa, Very Rev. Father Aaron Tanko said, Armed Fulani Militia stroke even in the presence of security operatives when they were conducting a mass burial of no fewer than 24 victims that were initially announced. According to the Chatholic Priest, the attack which claimed the lives of the victims of the mass burial occurred a fourth night ago and early hours of Saturday.